OL,3,CDirector of Public Health: Gambling
OL,4,C'likely' on the rise in Guernsey
OL,6,FThe report also assessed gambling
OL,7,Frates in the Isle of Man where more
OL,8,Fthan 75% of people said they gambled,
OL,9,Fand in Britain where the rate was
OL,10,Fsignificantly lower at 57%.
OL,12,FThe research, carried out by Liverpool
OL,13,FJohn Moores University, argues that
OL,14,Fthose who gamble are more likely to
OL,15,Fexperience ill-health, including
OL,16,Fhigher rates of obesity, addiction and
OL,17,Fviolence.
